Blood donor diagnosed with mad cow disease in France
Beef sold in Bulgaria since June 2004 has not been certified free ofmad cow disease because the test used is not officially recognised bythe European Union, mad-cow expert Roumen Valchovski said Friday.
Ireland suffers first suspected case of human form of mad cow disease
Canada, whose exports of beef products are effected by a single caseof  mad cow disease since may 2003, has exceeded its mad cow testingtarget for 2004, the Canadian Food Inspection Agency reported Sunday.
